<doc id="938451" wikidata="Q493803" url="?curid=938451" title="Charles Fambrough">
<text>Charles Fambrough (August 25, 1950January 1, 2011) was an American jazz bassist, composer and record producer from Philadelphia.

Fambrough was a member of Art Blakey&#x27;s Jazz Messengers during the early 1980s.

Suffering from kidney failure, congestive heart failure, and pulmonary hypertension, he died in 2011 at the age of 60.

