<doc id="938568" wikidata="Q847780" url="?curid=938568" title="Cycling at the 1908 Summer Olympics">
<text>At the 1908 Summer Olympics, seven track cycling events were contested, all for men only. The weather was poor, with rainfall causing the track to flood on occasion. The track was long (being built around the perimeter of the White City Stadium&#x27;s athletics track); some events (the 660 yards and the team pursuit) used full laps of the track; the others used metric distances.

